Made this for the 2nd time last night--this time I almost followed the recipe exactly. The few changes: sauteed a minced garlic clove with the other veggies, subbed 2% milk for the cream, added some Oriental red hot pepper sauce for zing. Used mostly flounder (was surprised how well it held up in this soup--I thought it would disintegrate, but it didn't). Added a few pre-cooked shrimp to get the 3/4 lbs. of fish. VERY, VERY YUMMY!!!

