Rating: 4
I made this tonight as a clam chowder, and would like to give the chowder 5 forks, if I could. Pretty much followed the recipe as written (which is unusual). The few changes I made were: 1) used 5 slices Louis Rich 65% Less Fat Turkey Bacon, 2) used about 3/4 - 1 lb. of potato, 3) used 8 oz. (drained weight) of minced clams, 5 fluid oz. of clam juice plus 3 fluid oz. of baked cod juice (all of these fish products had been frozen forever), 4) used 2% milk instead of heavy cream, 5) added some bottled hot pepper sauce for zing. Had to add a little extra milk at the end, as it seemed a bit thick. THIS IS AWESOME!!! Can't wait to try it with white fish fillets and fresh ingredients!!! (I wouldn't bother with the herbed oyster crackers again. Perhaps the recipe meant the spices to be powdered--my crushed ones did not coat the crackers and sat in glomps over some of the crackers. After baking the crackers they only tasted salty, as the salt I added did mix in with the unsalted butter.) HOWEVER, DO TRY THIS CHOWDER!!!

