Rating: 3
This is the most beautiful-looking chowder I have ever seen. I made it with halibut and cod, and found the fish to be a little too bland. Next time I'll probably try it with shrimp and salmon. We thought it needed just a little pepping up, and I'll also try it with a little garlic and thyme and a tiny bit of hot sauce added to the chowder. It's a very satisfying and good dish as it is, but I think that just a couple of tweaks would make it terrific.

Rating: 3
This was a fantastic recipe. Like most of us, we tweaked this recipe to our liking. For the fish we used 2 swordfish steaks, and also added 2 cloves of garlic, 1 1/2 teaspoons cayenne pepper and substituted half and half for the heavy cream. I think next time we will do the same and add some scallops. We've never had swordfish in a chowder before and we were kind of skeptical at first to use it. It turned out to be one of the best fish we've ever had in a chowder.

